<br>
As for a suggested hotkey, here's what I use.  /2 is the Healing Channel, and Complete Healing is in slot 4.<br>
<br>
/stand<br>
/cast 4<br>
/2 Complete Heal on [ %T ].<br>
/2 Next Cleric, --- SOMEONE ---<br>
/cast 4<br>
<br>
You can combine the healing messages onto one line, but I found the two lines better to catch the attention.<br>
<br>
As others have stated, some people can get confused if you name the Cleric specifically by name and then that Cleric dies.  In these situations it can be best to number the Clerics rather than name them.  However, in our guild, it goes something like this.<br>
<br>
Group Member tells the raid, 'Cleric02 down!'<br>
ClericNotInRotation tells the raid, 'I am now Cleric02'.<br>
<br>
ClericNotInRotation then takes their place in the rotation, and just looks for Cleric02's name in the NEXT CLERIC lines.<br>
<br>
