<br>
I wouldn't follow the /pauses from a few posts before me.  Some of the times are faster than they need to be.  Also, there are /pauses in there for some mobs where you do not need a CH chain.  Most mobs do not need a chain after they are slowed.  Those numbers seem to be only relying on a CH chain to keep the tank up.  It would be better to take a few clerics out of the chain to do quick heals (can also have someone keep a heal over time on the tank) when the mob does a damage spike.  That way the chain can slow down and less mana will be used overall.  It's better to not rely heavily on CH chains when it can be avoided.<br>
